Place the garlic, chillies, and ginger together in a food processor and process until smooth.Heat the oil in a frying pan or wok and fry the onion with the curry leaves for four minutes over a medium heat.Stir in the garlic, chilli and ginger mixture with the turmeric and salt.  Fry for two minutes, then add 100ml/3Â½fl oz coconut milk with 155ml/6fl oz boiling water.Simmer for two minutes and then add the fish pieces and gently simmer for 5-6 minutes.Add half of the tomato and the remaining coconut milk and simmer for 3-4 minutes.Garnish with the remaining chopped tomato.Serve with basmati rice.